<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>VISION:&nbsp;</strong></h4>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"} -->
<p class="wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">A community where youth of all genders and sexualities thrive.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->
<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>MISSION:&nbsp;</strong></h4>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>LYG empowers QTBIPoC/LGBTQIA+ youth to grow into healthy and resilient leaders through community connection, life skills education, and social advocacy.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list {"ordered":true} -->
<ol class="wp-block-list"><!-- wp:list-item {"style":{"elements":{"link":{"color":{"text":"#5933c2"}}},"color":{"text":"#5933c2"}}} -->
<li class="has-text-color has-link-color" style="color:#5933c2"><strong>Be a Brave Space –&nbsp;</strong>Create a transformative community of courageous growth, encouraging our youth to expand self-awareness, develop new perspectives, increase empathy, and cultivate hope.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item {"style":{"elements":{"link":{"color":{"text":"#478b92"}}},"color":{"text":"#478b92"}}} -->
<li class="has-text-color has-link-color" style="color:#478b92"><strong>Be Youth Centered</strong> –&nbsp;Rooted in the needs and interests of our youth and lead by their experience and direction.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item {"style":{"color":{"text":"#b21919"},"elements":{"link":{"color":{"text":"#b21919"}}}}} -->
<li class="has-text-color has-link-color" style="color:#b21919"><strong>Be Community Minded</strong> – Instill a sense of respect and responsibility for our world and fellow humankind through service, advocacy and activism.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item {"style":{"elements":{"link":{"color":{"text":"#8a8f26"}}},"color":{"text":"#8a8f26"}}} -->
<li class="has-text-color has-link-color" style="color:#8a8f26"><strong>Be Anti-Racist</strong> –&nbsp;Actively dismantle racism within ourselves, our organization, and our community.</li>
